    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "CAN Communication (F-CAN) Structure Description - Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "F-CAN （High-speed CAN）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The communication between powertrain/chassis control units is called F-CAN and uses High-speed CAN with a communication speed of 500 kbps."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1958_3.0_jpn_11390462_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Signal level detection by differential voltage"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In F-CAN, the differential voltage generated between the two communication lines (F-CAN_H and F-CAN_L) is detected and used as the signal level. No differential voltage is \"1\", This is a digital signal with the differential voltage set to \"0\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1958_3.0_jpn_11153883_3.0_disp.png"
    }
  ],
